title: 65th parallel south
text:
The 65th parallel south is a <a href="circle%20of%20latitude">circle of latitude</a> that is 65 <a href="degree%20%28angle%29">degrees</a> <a href="south">south</a> of the <a href="Earth">Earth's</a> <a href="equator">equatorial plane</a>. It crosses the <a href="Southern%20Ocean">Southern Ocean</a> and <a href="Antarctica">Antarctica</a>.
At this latitude the <a href="sun">sun</a> is visible for 22 hours, 02 minutes during the <a href="summer%20solstice">December solstice</a> and 3 hours, 35 minutes during the <a href="winter%20solstice">June solstice</a>.
